'''Empty Hills''', ''Pustye Kholmy'' or ''Pustye Holmy'' ({{lang-ru|Пустые холмы}}) is a non-commercial [[open-air concert|open-air]] alternative arts and [[music festival]] in [[Russia]].
The festival is held annually since 2003, usually over several days in June, in [[Kaluga Oblast]] or [[Smolensk Oblast]]. It is a non-profit event with no admission fee or sponsorship. The efforts of volunteers are responsible for the production of the event.{{cn|date=April 2015}}
Unlike most music festivals, ''Empty Hills'' has no specific musical format or style. Among genres represented on the festival, there are [[folk music]], [[blues]], [[rock music]], [[reggae]], sometimes [[electronic music]], [[jazz]] or [[avant-garde music|avant-garde]].[http://holmi.ru/en/]
== External links == * [http://holmi.ru/ Official site] {{icon ru}} * [http://holmi.ru/en/ Official site (English version)]
