{{Use American English|date=October 2018}}
{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}

[[File:Castell de Montjuïc Barcelona.jpg|thumb|View inside the [[Montjuïc Castle]]]]
[[File:Bombacorpus.jpg|thumb|Illustration of the Corpus Christi attack]]

The '''Montjuïc trial''' was a trial of anarchist suspects in the military [[Montjuïc Castle]] following the 1896 terrorist attack on the Barcelonean Corpus Christi procession. About 400 suspects were arrested, from whom 87 were put on trial and five executed. Stories of forced confessions through torture led to a 1898–1899 campaign for a [[judicial review]] of the trial organized through [[Alejandro Lerroux]] and his newspaper ''El Progreso''. [[Republican faction (Spanish Civil War)|Republican]] support for Lerroux from this action led to his rise as a left-wing force in Barcelona.<ref name="Smith">{{Cite book |last1=Smith |first1=Angel |chapter=Montjuïc trial |p=435 |title=Historical Dictionary of Spain |date=2009 |isbn=978-0-8108-5849-7 |edition=2nd |publisher=Scarecrow Press |df=mdy-all |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6y1BDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA448 |ref=harv }}</ref><ref name="Buffery">{{Cite book |chapter=Montjuïc trial |pp=245246 |last1=Buffery |first1=Helena |last2=Marcer |first2=Elisenda |title=Historical Dictionary of the Catalans |date=2010 |isbn=978-0-8108-5483-3 |publisher=Scarecrow Press |series=Historical Dictionaries of Peoples and Cultures |df=mdy-all }}</ref>

Anarchist [[Michele Angiolillo]] assassinated the [[Spanish Prime Minister]] [[Antonio Cánovas del Castillo]] in retaliation for his role in the trial and its executions.{{sfn|Smith|2009|p=130}}

