{{other uses2|Shalom}} {{inline citations|date=July 2014}} {{Infobox Newspaper | name = Şalom | image = | caption = | type = [[Weekly newspaper]] | format = [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|Tabloid]] | foundation = 29 October 1947 | ceased publication = | price = [[TL]] 2.30 Weekly, [[TL]] 120 Yearly [[subscription]] (2009) | owners = [[Gözlem Gazetecilik Basın ve Yayın A.Ş.]] | political position = [[Neutrality (philosophy)|Neutral]] | publisher = [[İvo Molinas]] | editor = [[Yakup Barokas]] | staff = | circulation = 5,000 weekly | headquarters = Atiye Sokak, Polar Apt. No 12/6, 30204 [[Teşvikiye]], [[İstanbul]], [[Turkey]] | ISSN = | website = [http://www.salom.com.tr/ ''Şalom'' official website] }}
'''''Şalom''''' is a [[Jewish]] [[weekly newspaper]] published in [[Turkey]]. Its name is the [[Turkish language|Turkish]] spelling of the [[Hebrew]] word [[Shalom|שלום (Shalom)]]. It was established on 29 October 1947 by the [[Turkish Jews|Turkish Jewish]] [[journalist]] [[Avram Leyon]]. It is printed in [[Istanbul]] and is published every Wednesday. Apart from one [[Ladino language|Ladino]] page, it is published in [[Turkish language|Turkish]]. [[İvo Molinas]] is its publisher, and [[Yakup Barokas]] is its [[editor in chief]]. Its circulation is about 5,000.
